I'd like the option to use foreground indexing if it would help increase the speed for index recovery.

Our cold standby doesn't have an index at all, so if we were to recover it, it would show zero issues with the empty index. Since it's pretty unusable in that state, why not allow us to use foreground reindex when recovering to speed it up? Our current index backup is 2.4GB zipped. It would mean we could reduce our interval to once a day if the recovery speed improves.

