At the moment, newly created issues will be sent in a notification which reads something like the following which clearly state that the issue is newly created.
{code}Admin created an issue{code}

When an issue is updated, it will read the following which again clearly states that this is not a new issue
{code}Admin updated an issue{code}

However, when a user receives a lot of emails from JIRA daily about newly created or updated issues, it won't be as easy to differentiate the newly created issues from the updated issues. As some users (eg. managers) are only interested in newly created issues, it would be great if the default template clearly states that the issue is newly created. Then these users can easily differentiate newly created issues from updated issues. For example
